The course enables students to acquire fundamental knowledge and skills of how to design and conduct educational research.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to support students to become investigative teachers and develop their  understanding of the essence of educational research.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course students will: 1.	understand the importance of educational research and dissemination of pedagogical knowledge in the teacher's job; 2.	analyze and evaluate the essence of educational research (including research ethics) and the research process; 3.	analyze and evaluate the most common research designs as well as data collection and analysis methods in educational research; can apply these in designing and conducting their research; 4.	analyze and evaluate research in terms of quality criteria; 5.	apply different data analysis software; 6.	be able to plan action research.
